China's gross domestic product expanded 4.8% year-on-year in the first quarter of 2022, the National Bureau of Statistics said on Monday. But it is below China's annual target of 5.5%, and it reflects pressure from the COVID-19 pandemic and the conflict between Russia and Ukraine. However, the situation is improving. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Zheng Junfeng says that with government policy support, normality will resume soon and China's annual growth target is achievable.